Sentencas: A computational model is developed to represent the coupled behavior of elementary chemistry, electrochemistry, and transport in the vicinity of solid-oxide fuel cell three-phase boundaries.
Titulo: Modeling Electrochemical Oxidation of Hydrogen on Ni-YSZ Pattern Anodes

Sentencas: The model is applied to assist the development and evaluation of H-2 charge-transfer reaction mechanisms for Ni-yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anodes.
Titulo: Modeling Electrochemical Oxidation of Hydrogen on Ni-YSZ Pattern Anodes

Sentencas: Elementary chemistry and surface transport for the Ni and YSZ surfaces are derived from prior literature.
Titulo: Modeling Electrochemical Oxidation of Hydrogen on Ni-YSZ Pattern Anodes

Sentencas: Previously published patterned-anode experiments [J. Mizusaki , Solid State Ionics, 70/71, 52 (1994)] are used to evaluate alternative electrochemical charge-transfer mechanisms.
Titulo: Modeling Electrochemical Oxidation of Hydrogen on Ni-YSZ Pattern Anodes

Sentencas: The results show that a hydrogen-spillover mechanism can explain the Mizusaki polarization measurements over wide ranges of gas-phase composition with both anodic and cathodic biases.
Titulo: Modeling Electrochemical Oxidation of Hydrogen on Ni-YSZ Pattern Anodes
